# Build-context ignore for the playwright-runner image (build context is
# this dir; runner/Dockerfile COPYs only package.json, source is bind-
# mounted at runtime via compose `.:/work`).
#
# Excludes:
#   * nginx-certs/ — nginx-cert-init writes nginx.key as root-owned 0600.
#     With the classic (non-buildx) builder the docker CLI tars the
#     context as the invoking user; a non-root local dev can't read the
#     key and the build dies with "checking context: no permission to
#     read .../nginx-certs/nginx.key". CI builds as root so never hit it.
#     The runner trusts the CA over the network at runtime — it never
#     needs the key in its image. Also basic hygiene: a private key has
#     no business in a build context.
#   * runtime artifacts (reports, results, node_modules) — large, never
#     COPYd, only bloat the context tarball.
nginx-certs/
test-results/
playwright-report/
node_modules/
infra/
